ASHS volume data: 2022-02-15

Source: R/data.R
PICSLASHS.Rd

ASHS volume data: 2022-02-15 data. More information is available at https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Usage

data(PICSLASHS)

Format

A data frame with 1978 observations and 59 variables.

Source

https://adni.loni.usc.edu/data-samples/adni-data/

Details

  • ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , with options: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3

  • COLPROT factor Study protocol of data collection , with factor levels: ADNI1, ADNIGO, ADNI2, ADNI3, ADNI4

  • RID numeric roster participant ID Range value: 21, ..., 6971

  • VISCODE character visit code

  • VISCODE2 character visit code translated

  • EXAMDATE Date Date of MRI scan Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • ICV numeric Intercranial volume derived from T1 image Range value: 999281, ..., 1976566

  • SLICE_THICKNESS numeric Coronal slice thickness Range value: 1.99923, ..., 2.2

  • LEFT_CA1_VOL numeric left hemisphere ROI CA1 volume Range value: 43.03, ..., 5584.1

  • LEFT_CA1_NS numeric Number of coronal slices in which left hemisphere ROI CA1 appears Range value: 2, ..., 26

  • LEFT_CA2_VOL numeric left hemisphere ROI CA2 volume Range value: 0, ..., 7.935

  • LEFT_CA2_NS numeric Number of coronal slices in which left hemisphere ROI CA2 appears Range value: 0, ..., 9

  • LEFT_CA3_VOL numeric left hemisphere ROI CA3 volume Range value: 0, ..., 126.342

  • LEFT_CA3_NS numeric Number of coronal slices in which left hemisphere ROI CA3 appears Range value: 0, ..., 11

  • LEFT_DG_VOL numeric left hemisphere ROI dentate gyrus volume Range value: 8.85, ..., 2496.64

  • T2_QC_R character manual QC score for right hemisphere image quality -1=no image;0=Unusable (substructures and the SRLM are not identifiable) or image has motion and looks blurry/wiggly;1=Bad Quality (SRLM is hard to identify and substructures are blurry) or image has motion;2=Adequate Quality (some substructures are clear, SRLM is mostly visible);3=intermediate quality between 2 & 4;4=Good Quality (most substructures are clear, SRLM is continuously visible) Decoded Value: Yes

  • T2_QC_L character manual QC score for left hemisphere image quality -1=no image;0=Unusable (substructures and the SRLM are not identifiable) or image has motion and looks blurry/wiggly;1=Bad Quality (SRLM is hard to identify and substructures are blurry) or image has motion;2=Adequate Quality (some substructures are clear, SRLM is mostly visible);3=intermediate quality between 2 & 4;4=Good Quality (most substructures are clear, SRLM is continuously visible) Decoded Value: Yes
